Other Improvements to Custom Fuel Framework

Improve carbon accounting by implementing these enhancements: Use the developer name instead of record identifiers to capture the API names of custom fuels and custom units of measure. Address the gallons unit discrepancy in vehicle asset energy use for custom fuels. Use standard weight units for custom fuels.

Where: This change applies to Lightning Experience in Professional, Enterprise, Unlimited, and Developer editions with the Net Zero Cloud Starter or Growth license.

Why: These improvements enhance the accuracy of carbon accounting for custom fuels and units of measure.

For custom fuel, if the NamespacePrefix exists, the API name for fuel type is {NamespacePrefix_}custom_{DeveloperName of the FuelType object}, otherwise itâ€™s custom_{DeveloperName of the FuelType object}. For a custom unit of measure, if the NamespacePrefix exists, the API name for the unit of measure is {NamespacePrefix_}custom_{DeveloperName of the SustainabilityUom object}, otherwise it is custom_{DeveloperName of the SustainabilityUom object}.

Make sure backward compatibility in carbon emissions calculations by using US Gallons unit of measure in vehicle asset energy use fuels instead of Gallons. Use standard weight or mass units of measure (lbs, Kg, long tons, short tons, tonnes) for a custom fuel to calculate its carbon emissions. Ensure that the conversion to standard units, Kwh or GJ, for the custom fuel type is specified and the correct emissions factor is applied to accurately calculate emissions.
title: Improvements to Custom Fuel Framework
